node.text: what do you use?
Bellissime 👏👏👏

Coming to you from deep in the Galapagos. 🐊 Incredible shots by @danabjarner using Sony Alpha 7 IV. “My goal with these captures was to create a composition that embodies the essence of Fernandina Island. Inspired by its vibrant colors and textures, I focused on the marine iguanas and their remarkable adaptations to the harsh volcanic environment. These iguanas symbolize survival and resilience, thriving in such a challenging habitat. Through this composition, I aimed to select both the beauty and the harsh realities of this extraordinary ecosystem.” - Dana. #SonyAlpha
@yourdailynaturefix our favorite too 🔥
Holy smokes that first shot is incredible!
I use my a7iv for wildlife 😍 One day I should be so lucky to visit this island 👏👏👏
It’s a beauty of an all rounder camera! I use it for everything I do it’s very versatile
@meuffatale oh yeahhhh 😂😂😂
@lo_ne.r so the world has some hope with us in it! gotcha
@meuffatale we always have a place to fit in !! 🙌❤
Godzilla that you ? 😍😮😮😮
First photo… Godzilla? Second photo… Baby Godzilla.
@gfxkid indeed it is 🫶🏼🫶🏼
@gfxkid it really is 🙌🙌
@gfxkid need a lens to
That camera is the best!!!
@amhed.sm11 we love to hear that! Thank you for sharing, keep up the good work 👏👏

I use my A7IV for everything literally!! Since it’s the only camera I have, I use it for sports Photography as well of weekly vlogs! MMA videos and Photos of Artists performing!! I really love the A 7IV I think I will remember this camera as the camera that changed my life! 🫶🏼📸🎥💪🏼
The best purchase I made within the last few days 🔥 such a good camera! 📸
Using the a7 IV for all my works, for travels and for fun. Coming from an a7 II it has been upgrade

The A7IV is almost the perfect camera. It needs 4K 60fps uncropped, 4K HS 30fps for lower file sizes, much better IBIS and AI Autofocus. Other than that, the versatility is incredible. I shoot many things simultaneously, switching photo and video is fast and reliable. I have 2 A7IV’s I use for interview set ups, the resolution is amazing, way better than the A7S3 (which I bought and sold), the dynamic range is also incredible. Button layout is perfect. It has never overheat on me, especially because I shoot long form 4K. Lots of nitpicking to do for the rest like in camera LUT’s, anamorphic de-squeeze with autofocus, better quality brighter screen, open gate recording, but these are all extra’s. As someone who uses the A7IV for photo and video work, it’s almost the perfect camera.
I used for everything, theres no limits!

I got the a7IV for its hybrid capability because I was shooting high photo and video content. I have an FX3 now and use my a7IV for primarily photo and an occasional B cam. I love the picture quality as well as the dynamic range. I feel that even in low light situation it keeps the detail super well and I'm able to bring it out in post. Images are always so sharp and I love it!!!
Crazy shots🔥😍

I use the A7iv for concert photography and video because it is the perfect hybrid camera. Low light capability with 10bit color make it the only camera in need on the road. Keeps my bag light and my wallet a little heavier.
These are so cool! I love my A7 IV and use it mostly for outdoor adventures landscape photography! The low light ability always amazes me.
Incredible shots 😍 well done 👏

Mostly used for wildlife photography but I purchased it as a lovely hybrid camera for videography too, also super happy with the update for focus bracketing that was a great addition. Only draw back is in wildlife sometimes I’d like the extra 17mp of an A1
Using both for video and photo. Some kind of theatrical performances and it’s perfect for it 😌🤝 (also commercials and clips)
Love this cam - every feature is so well thought out!

I’ve been using two A7iv’s for weddings since they launched, with mainly the 50mm 1.2 GM, and 35mm 1.4 GM, and they’ve never missed a beat or let me down. Amazing cameras that just let me do what I do and the image quality is just sublime ❤️

I use mine for professional portraits and branding shoots and absolutely love the color science behind this power house of camera. I came from the Riii and I felt like most of the cameras that came out between the Riii and iV weren’t enough of an upgrade or had a downside. For me it’s the MP, Color Science, and sturdier body. #homerun
So sharp 😮 - getting IN there @danabjarner 🙌
